 & TimberTech Certified"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"children":[["$","svg",null,{"width":"20","height":"20","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Multi-level & single-level custom designs"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"children":[["$","svg",null,{"width":"20","height":"20","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Screened porches, pergolas & outdoor kitchens"}]]}],["$","li","3",{"children":[["$","svg",null,{"width":"20","height":"20","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Full HOA submission management"}]]}],["$","li","4",{"children":[["$","svg",null,{"width":"20","height":"20","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"5-Star Google Rated - call (571) 655-7207"}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}]
6:["$","section",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__section","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__container","children":[["$","div","0",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__textBlock","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__subTitle","children":"Top Deck Design Ideas for Northern Virginia in 2026"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Northern Virginia homeowners are investing more than ever in their outdoor living spaces, and 2026 is shaping up to be the biggest year yet for custom deck design in the region. From Loudoun County to Fairfax, the demand for premium multi-level decks, screened porches, and full outdoor living environments has never been higher. At Loudoun Decks, we build these spaces every day - and we know exactly what works for Northern Virginia homes."]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["The most requested deck design in 2026 is the multi-level composite deck with integrated features. Homeowners want more than just a platform - they want a complete outdoor room. That means built-in seating, outdoor kitchens, pergola shade structures, and seamless transitions from the interior living space to the backyard. These full-featured decks typically range from $35,000 to $75,000 and completely transform the function and value of your property."]}],["$","p","2",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Whether you are starting from scratch or remodeling an existing deck, Loudoun Decks has the design expertise and installation credentials to bring your vision to life. We are a Trex Platinum Partner and TimberTech Certified contractor - meaning we have access to the full product catalog and deliver builds backed by the industry's best warranties."]}]]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__textBlock","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__subTitle","children":"Composite Deck Design Trends: Trex & TimberTech in Northern Virginia"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Composite decking has completely taken over the Northern Virginia market, and for good reason. Materials like Trex Transcend and TimberTech AZEK offer the look of natural wood without the maintenance burden - no sealing, no staining, no rotting. For Northern Virginia homeowners who deal with hot, humid summers and freezing winters, composite is the clear choice for longevity."]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["In 2026, the design trend in composite decking is moving toward richer, darker color palettes - deep grays, warm browns, and earthy tones that complement the natural landscapes of Loudoun and Fairfax counties. Two-tone deck designs, where the field boards and border boards use contrasting colors, are especially popular for adding visual definition and custom character."]}],["$","p","2",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Our team helps homeowners navigate the full range of composite options - from entry-level composite to the premium capped polymer lines - matching materials to budget, aesthetics, and HOA requirements. Every composite deck we install comes with a full manufacturer warranty and our workmanship guarantee."]}]]}],"$L12"]}],"$L13"]}]}]
7:["$","section",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__section","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__header","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__title","children":"Why Northern Virginia Homeowners Choose Loudoun Decks"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__description","children":"We are not a franchise. We are a local Loudoun County team with the design expertise, premium certifications, and local track record to deliver Northern Virginia's best outdoor living spaces."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__grid","children":[["$","div","0",{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__card","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__iconWrapper","children":["$","svg",null,{"width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}]}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__itemTitle","children":"2026 Design Trends"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__itemDesc","children":"We stay ahead of the curve with the latest deck design trends for Northern Virginia - from multi-level composite decks to integrated outdoor kitchens and louvered pergolas."}]]}]]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__card","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__iconWrapper","children":["$","svg",null,{"width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}]}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__itemTitle","children":"Custom Plans for Every Home"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__itemDesc","children":"Every deck design we create is fully custom. We work with your lot, your HOA requirements, and your lifestyle to deliver a design that is uniquely yours."}]]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__card","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__iconWrapper","children":["$","svg",null,{"width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}]}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__itemTitle","children":"Trex & TimberTech Certified"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"ServiceInclusions-module__sDDdhG__itemDesc","children":"As a Trex Platinum Partner and TimberTech Certified installer, we bring the best materials and the highest installation standards to every Northern Virginia project."}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}]
