e project will move forward."}]}]]}]}]}],["$","div","3",{"className":"ProcessSteps-module__7tzpxa__stepRow","style":{"backgroundColor":"#ffffff"},"children":"$L14"}]]}]
9:["$","$L15",null,{"title":"Deck Design Ideas Northern Virginia 2026 - FAQs","faqs":[{"q":"What are the top deck design trends in Northern Virginia for 2026?","a":"In 2026, Northern Virginia homeowners are gravitating toward multi-level composite decks, integrated outdoor kitchens, louvered pergola covers, built-in LED lighting, and seamless indoor-outdoor transitions. Low-maintenance Trex and TimberTech materials dominate the market."},{"q":"How much does a custom deck cost in Northern Virginia in 2026?","a":"A custom composite deck in Northern Virginia typically ranges from $22,000 to $65,000+, depending on size, material selection, design complexity, and add-ons such as pergolas, screened porches, or outdoor kitchens."},{"q":"What deck materials are most popular in Northern Virginia?","a":"Composite decking - especially Trex and TimberTech - is the most popular choice in Northern Virginia due to its durability, low maintenance, and resistance to the region's humid summers and cold winters. Pressure-treated wood remains an option for budget-conscious builds."},{"q":"Do I need a permit to build a deck in Northern Virginia?","a":"Yes. All deck builds in Northern Virginia require permits from the local county - Loudoun, Fairfax, or Prince William. Loudoun Decks handles the full permitting process, including HOA submissions, structural drawings, and inspections."},{"q":"Can Loudoun Decks help with deck design ideas for my specific home?","a":"Absolutely. We offer free consultations and custom design proposals for homeowners across Northern Virginia. Our design team will evaluate your space, your HOA requirements, and your vision to create a fully custom outdoor living plan."},{"q":"What is the best deck design for a small backyard in Northern Virginia?","a":"For smaller backyards, we recommend elevated single-level decks with built-in bench seating and under-deck storage, or a compact multi-functional deck with a pergola to maximize vertical space and shade."}]}]
